value.value: The treatment involving exposure of plant to the rice hoja blanca virus. It is a causal agent for rice hoja blanca disease.
A plant exposure (PECO:0001001) involving the application of a biotic or biological factor such as a microbe, insect, animal, or plant or a combination thereof.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to the rice grassy stunt virus. It is a causal agent for rice grassy stunt disease.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to the barley yellow dwarf virus. It is a causal agent for rice Giallume disease.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to the rice gall dwarf virus. It is a causal agent for rice gall dwarf disease.

The treatment involving exposure of plant to the pathogen Balansia oryzae-sativae. It is a causal agent for rice Udbatta diesase which is also called as Black Choke Disease, False Ergot Disease, Incense Rod Disease.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to the pathogen Magnaporthe salvinii. It is a causal agent for rice stem rot disease and Seedling Blight (Fungal) Disease.

The treatment involving exposure of plant to the pathogen Rhizoctonia oryzae. It is a causal agent for rice Sheath Spot disease such as Bordered Sheath Spot Disease, Red Sclerotial Disease and Rhizoctonia Sheath Spot Disease.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to the pathogen rice dwarf virus. It is a causal agent for rice dwarf phytoreo virus disease.

label.value: rice black streak dwarf virus exposure

value.value: The treatment involving exposure of plant to the pathogen rice black streak dwarf virus. It is a causal agent for rice blast steak dwarf disease.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to the pest Aphelenchoides besseyi. It is a causal agent for rice white tip nematode disease.
The treatment involving an exposure to above optimal water temperature, which may depend on the study type or the regional environment.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to the pest Meloidogyne salasi.

definition.value: Meloidogyne salasi is a causal agent for rice root-knot nematode disease.

value.value: The treatment involving exposure of plant to the pest Meloidogyne oryzae.

definition.value: Meloidogyne oryzae is a causal agent for rice root-knot nematode disease.

value.value: The treatment involving exposure of plant to the pest Meloidogyne javanica.

definition.value: Meloidogyne javanica is a causal agent for rice root-knot nematode disease.

value.value: The treatment involving exposure of plant to the pest Meloidogyne incognita.

definition.value: Meloidogyne incognita is a causal agent for rice root-knot nematode disease.

value.value: The treatment involving exposure of plant to the pathogen Cylindrocladium scoparium. It is a causal agent for rice Sheath Net Blotch Disease.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to the pest Meloidogyne graminicola.

definition.value: Meloidogyne graminicola is a causal agent for rice root-knot nematode disease.

value.value: The treatment involving exposure of plant to the pathogen Pyrenochaeta oryzae. It is a causal agent for rice Sheath Blotch Disease.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to the pathogen Athelia rolfsii. It is a causal agent for rice Seedling Blight (Fungal) disease.
A plant fungal exposure (PECO:0007233) involving exposure of plant to the pathogen Sarocladium oryzae. It is a causal agent for rice Seedling Blight (Fungal) disease and/or Sheath Rot disease.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to the pathogen Thanatephorus cucumeris.

definition.value: It is a causal agent for rice Sheath Blight diseases  such as Brown-bordered Leaf and Sheath Spot disease and/or Oriental Leaf and Sheath Blight disease.

value.value: The treatment involving an exposure to wind, which may depend on regional environment.
The treatment involving an exposure to watering frequencies.
The treatment involving an exposure to frost or freezing air temperature, which may depend on the study type or the regional environment. This temperature is either below or around 4C.

The treatment to plants or the populations grown in the regions where the land is leveled, may have bunded fields with water control, shallow. For rice flooded with anaoerobic soil during crop growth.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to the pathogen Gerlachia oryzae. It is a causal agent for a form of rice Seedling Blight (Fungal) disease.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to micronutrient manganese as supplement to study various types of responses.

The treatment involving exposure of plant to the pathogen Alternaria padwickii. It is a causal agent for rice seedling blight (fungal) disease and/or stackburn disease also called as Alternaria Leaf Spot Disease.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to the pathogen Gibberella zeae. It is a causal agent for rice Scab disease.

The treatment involving the plant or the populations grown in regions where the land level is slightly steep, noncontinuous flooding of variable depth and duration. Alternatingconditions of aerobic to anaerobic soil.
The treatment involving the plant or the populations grown in regions where the land level is steep, rarely flodded and has aerobic soil.
The treatment involving an exposure to the conditions found in a type of biome characterized by low moisture levels and infrequent and unpredictable precipitation of rainfall.

A treatment in terms of plant's exposure to the regional conditions found in the vicinity of the water bodies like, sea, river, lake etc. Growth conditions may include aerobic to anaerobic soil,  salinity or toxicity in tidal areas. Treatment may include standing or flash flooding.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to macronutrient phosphorus as supplement to study various types of responses.

The treatment involving the plant or the populations grown in regions that are adjacent to the tropics, usually roughly defined as the ranges 25-40 N and 25-40 S latitude. These areas typically have hot tropical summers, but non-tropical winters.
The treatment involving an exposure to frost or  freezing water temperature, which may depend on the study type or the regional environment. This temperature is either below or around 4C.
The treatment involving the plant or the populations grown in regions where the land is excessively dry and receives insufficient rainfall to support agriculture.
The treatment involving the plant or the populations grown in regions where the total annual rainfall received in the range of 25-50cm (10-20 inches).
A chemical exposure (PECO:0007189) that involves the use of a fungal elicitor to study various types of plant responses.
A plant exposure (PECO:0001001) where there is a lack of information describing the experimental conditions.

definition.value: In some cases, only the study type (PECO:0007231) is known, without any additional information about the treatments.

value.value: A hydroponic plant culture media exposure (PECO:0007067) which is an exposure to Hoagland solution during growth.

definition.value: The Hoagland solution, originally intended to imitate a (nutrient-) rich soil solution, has high concentrations of N and K so it is very well suited for the development of large plants like tomato and bell pepper. (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hoagland_solution)

value.value: An organic chemical exposure (PECO:0001003) involving the application of  methyl jasmonate (MeJa; CHEBI:15929).
An organic chemical exposure (PECO:0001003) involving the application of the tryptophan (Trp) analog 5-methyltryptophan (5MT; CHEBI: 52446).
A growth hormone exposure (PECO:0007165) involving the use of brassinosteroid (or its homolog).
A fungal elicitor exposure (PECO:0007402) that involves the use of a cerebroside elicitor to study various types of plant responses.
